        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 13 at 9:28PM MDT until June 13 at 10:30PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>SVRBYZ

The National Weather Service in Billings has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Eastern Big Horn County in south central Montana...
Southwestern Carter County in southeastern Montana...
Southwestern Custer County in southeastern Montana...
Powder River County in southeastern Montana...
Southern Rosebud County in southeastern Montana...
Northeastern Sheridan County in north central Wyoming...

* Until 1030 PM MDT.

* At 928 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 26 miles
southeast of Ashland, or 33 miles west of Broadus, moving
southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
hail damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.
Expect wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Broadus, Biddle, Volborg, Ridgeway, Olive, Sonnette, Moorhead,
Belle Creek, Boyes, Ridge, Otter, Hammond and Northern Cheyenne
Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.</instruction>
